As a Qualified Breathwork Facilitator,  Women's Empowerment Coach and Men's Intimacy Coach, Jaiyde  shares her soothing voice with many of her guided Breath Journeys and Meditations.  

Ride the breath with Jaiyde and drop into states of deep bliss, surrender and healing....read more
I am a passionate zen meditator and coach developing healthy and productive routines and helping others to reboot theirs.

Josh Kane is a music producer and yoga teacher from New Haven, CT.  He offers guided meditations, yoga classes and sound healing in the tradition of Bhakti Yoga (devotional service to God).  He has a very direct and passionate approach to spirituality, and believes meditation should be kept simple because the mind is complicated enough.  His meditations are deeply insightful, well-rounded and easy for people of all ages and backgrounds to connect with.    ...read more

Jade Honce is a Creative Arts Therapist and Clinical Counsellor offering her services virtually in Canada. Her meditations support the process of nervous system regulation, emotional expression and containment, and a deeper sense of connection to one’s self and to others. She has been told by many that her voice is deeply soothing and supportive to meditation, so she began sharing her voice with others outside of her practice through Insight Timer....read more

Julia Williamson is a professional singer, songwriter, voice coach, healer and founder of Sing to Thrive which is a boutique voice transformational coaching agency built on the philosophy that when you find your voice, you transform your life. Julia's 20+ years of work in this area is very grounded and practical, mixed with joy and powerful healing tools merging the potent healing power of singing, neuroplasticity and music frequency that has profound results....read more

Passionate about living a fulfilled life, and making the most out of each moment, James is the perfect person to help you achieve your vision and dreams. Having started his first business as a guitar teacher when he was still in high school, James has successfully begun and operated interesting and innovative businesses for 20 years. One of James’s current ventures ‘Cosmic Tone’ is an instrument manufacturing business which has been operating since 2011. These musical instruments are loved by many people, and are now being purchased and played worldwide. James also performs music and relaxing soundbaths with his wife Michelle on a regular basis, and loves witnessing the uplifting effect experienced by participants....read more

Julia möchte dich in deiner Balance unterstützen. Als zertifizierte Meditationskursleiterin und geprüfte Coach bringt sie ihre Expertise aus den Bereichen Achtsamkeit und Persönlichkeitsentwicklung ein.

Hafa Adai!  I'm an island girl from Guam and proud to be a part of the AAPI community here on Insight Timer.  I'm excited to explore and lead you through your meditation practice.  As a dancer, performer, and thought of as a highly empathic person, I believe we are complex beings and are always a yin and yang across many spectrums and plains all at the same time.  So, we are always evolving together.  I enjoy helping you feel confident and accomplished in mind, body, and spirit. ...read more

Josie is an artist and meditation teacher (trained with the British School of Meditation) who believes in the power of creativity to transform lives. Much of her work involves finding nuggets of joy in the everyday to nurture us and build a resilient self....read more

Jo is a Business Coach, Messaging Strategist and Energy Curator.  
She brings her experience as a certified Pranic Healer, together with her passion for breathwork and spiritual practices to release the doing, pushing and striving energy that so many driven, ambitious women feel so they can create their next level of success in building wildly successful businesses....read more

Self-taught pianist & composer based in the UK. 

Playing since childhood, James has always sought to express musically what moves deep within us all and find connection with himself & others in that emotional space.

Oftentimes reflective, sometimes melancholic, always a musical adventure into the soul.

His hope is that his music helps you find your way home to yourself. 

As James writes: "Take a breath. Be still. Fall deeply into your own arms. Take hold of your own hand that is always outstretched waiting for you to come home. I'll meet you there."

As well as performing in his own right, James has collaborated in workshops with personal development coaches, dance teachers, yoga instructors and Contact Improvisation facilitators, as well as created bespoke musical pieces to accompany guided meditations for commissioning authors....read more

Jessica is an intuitive reader, light language channel, manifestation coach, Starseed and Lightworker. She lives in Florida with her husband and dog, and her mission here is to help awaken and activate other beautiful souls to fulfill their life purpose....read more

Jörg Eberhardt leitet seit 2001 Seminare für Mitarbeiter, Gründer und Unternehmer. Er ist seit über 20 Jahren als Unternehmensberater und Gründercoach tätig. Seine Schwerpunktthemen sind: Lesen im morphischen Feld, Zwiegespräche, Magie des Jetzt und Zukunfts-Club. Meditation, Yoga und Tai Chi gehören zu seiner persönlichen Praxis. Er unterstützt die „Ökonomie der Herzen“ mit seiner Arbeit....read more

John Vegard Schow has been composing and producing music for a wide audience
for many years. He specializes in conveying meanings through instrumental music and constantly explores how far he can draw the listener. In his music he reinvites the listener to an oasis of emotion, mood and tranquility. He does not dictate what the listener should feel, but encourages taking part in the journey, grasping the surroundings and indulging in the sensory impressions we are exposed to while listening to the music....read more

Juliana Zappitell is a certified E-RYT 200/YACEP Vinyasa and Yin Yoga instructor from Santa Barbara, CA. She specializes in trauma-informed practices. Juliana was introduced to yoga in 2012 in by a close friend and since she has found solace in her practice during significant life transitions. Juliana started her own yoga community when she moved across the country during the global pandemic. She facilitated a safe space for UC Santa Barbara students living in uncertain times to move their body and connect with each other. She did this through starting a wellness blog and incorporating weekly hybrid yoga and meditation classes. As businesses began to re-open, she stumbled upon Yoga Soup and immediately felt at home. She has taught there for the past year and is now running a women's circle and hosting a retreat in Mexico. She furthered her understanding of the mind-body connection by completing an "Anatomy of Trauma" training and taking several courses in Hinduism and Psychology....read more

Jenna Grayson, C.HT., HTP brings a holistic and integrative approach to her work, recognizing the power of energy medicine to restore wholeness to the person. 

Jenna specializes in helping people transcend the limitations of anxiety, fear, and limiting beliefs. She has a background in mental health, energy healing and hypnotherapy. She worked as a social worker for over 8 years and has also taught groups in hypnotherapy, EFT, and energy medicine. 

Jenna studied energy medicine at the Scripps Center for Integrative Medicine and Hypnotherapy at the Hypnosis Motivation Institute. She has taught hypnosis and energy medicine internationally and has traveled to over 30 countries on 6 continents.  She now resides in Southern California where she has a private practice and does stand-up comedy in Hollywood, CA....read more

Jarrien is the Founder of Arden, an organisation that focusses on supporting people to become the best versions of themselves, and to believe in their unlimited potential.

She is a qualified and accredited Life Coach and Mindfulness Practitioner with a huge passion to serve others.

Jarrien helps others to live a fuller life by building natural resilience and unleashing untapped purpose and motivation....read more

Jane Mejlhede er spirituel lærer, psykoterapeut, healer og underviser i forskellige former for personlig og spirituel udvikling og transformation med fokus på nærvær og bevidsthed.
Hendes vision er at støtte andre i at mærke, hvem de er udover personligheden.
Oprindeligt uddannet Cand. Mag. i dansk og kommunikation fra Aarhus Universitet. Holistisk psykoterapeut, NLP og Enneagram Master Trainer. Akasha Master Healer, Trainer & Initiator....read more

Blessings
Jacqueline has been walking, living and sharing the inner journey for over 20 years. 
The western medical way she walked (Nurse for 35 years) & intense physical & mental challenges led her to understand that unless the Spiritual Journey is undertaken nothing is ever fully healed. 
Seeking inside herself she found the Light within her own Heart.

She offers her own open, clear, heart as a Light, to guide each to their own opening, clear, heart.
May Your day be Blessed with Gentle Grace....read more

Jess is a deeply embodied yoga instructor, writer, and soon to be yoga therapist practicing around NY, USA and studying at Maryland University of Integrative Health for a Master's of Science of Yoga Therapy. She teaches yin yoga, vinyasa yoga, and mindful movement classes combining elements of qigong that facilitate in grounding anxiety and encouraging a sense of intimate connection to the Self. Through her work, she aims to provide a space of comfort, connection, expansion and safety for all....read more

Jordan is a licensed perinatal mental health therapist here to help pregnant people and busy parents find accessible ways to practice mindfulness, increase mind/body connection and foster a sense of internal awareness calm.

Jordan is a licensed clinical social worker (LCSW) with extensive training, education and lived experience supporting the mind/body connection. She integrates clinical theory with her mindfulness and somatic therapy training to provide accessible introductions to mindfulness and meditation. Jordan also completed her certification in perinatal mental health (PMH-C) through Postpartum Support International and is passionate about supporting birthing and non-birthing parents using mindfulness and self-compassion....read more

For the last decade Justyna has been coaching high-achieving women in unlocking their feminine power. Helping them reignite fulfilling love relationships, without  losing themselves in the process and bringing the best out of their men.

A former gold medallist athlete, masters scholar in chemical engineering and sacred retreats teacher. Justyna offers a unique, leading-edge approach by combining peak performance mindset and trauma healing.  

Justyna’s clients have had brilliant results including finding new love, healing their relationship, getting married, having a baby and starting their own business. 

With a warm and welcoming approach, Justyna supports her clients in a safe and playful environment helping them align heart, mind and desire for a powerful transformation and proven results. ...read more

Jules Febre was born and raised in a section of New York City known as the Lower East Side. At the age of 13, Jules spent three months in India; two of which were spent in Mysore studying Ashtanga Yoga with Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois. During that time he was invited to share satsang with Swami Nirmalananda and Shyam Das, two radical yogis that have each contributed greatly to the progression of yoga in the West. At the age of 16 Jules began working at the Jivamukti Yoga School helping to clean, and is now considered one of the leading teachers of the Jivamukti Yoga method, teaching the method world wide as well as facilitating at the very highly regarded teacher training programs. 

Teaching yoga is Jules’ passion. He is grateful to his teachers, Sharonji (Gannon), Davidji (Life) who he has had the privilege of studying with for over 15 years, for igniting his devotion to the Jivamukti Yoga practice and for inspiring countless students around the world. ...read more
Janus Haastrup is a poet, philosopher, therapist, and long-time meditator based out of Copenhagen.

In 1995 I was 24 years old, and I was getting disenfranchised with human folly. I realized my own suffering was just a reflection of what the whole world was going through.  That was when I saw (and then read) "Seven Years in Tibet", and I was floored by the level of compassion the Buddhists exuded.  It was a revelation that such commitment to non-harm could completely revamp human life if more people adopted it. So, I began to meditate, after reading some really simple instructions, which I worked with alone for years.  Breathe in for 3 counts, hold for 3 counts, and release for 3 counts, and repeat.

Now if I'm going to help you on this journey, I need to tell you a not-so-secret secret.  The last sentence in the previous paragraph is honestly all you need.  That simple practice took me from fully self-absorbed, to a full blown kundalini awakening in 2000.  I then learned Kriya yoga from Paramahamsa Prajnanananda, and Trika yoga and the Sri Chakra Puja from Swami Chetanananda....read more

Although coming from a rocky upbringing, he never failed to look for the silver lining while staying busy with creative endeavours. By a shocking twist of fate, he was introduced to something unexpected that would alter the direction of his life forever – controlled breathing. This relatively untapped field immediately resonated with Johannes, and he has since relentlessly cultivated knowledge on the subject from brilliant minds such as Wim Hof, Laird Hamilton, and many others....read more

Jessica is a women's empowerment and embodiment coach, supporting women to let go of limiting beliefs and move towards their visions with inner trust and a deep sense of self-love. You will find ease in taking aligned actions which deeply resonate with your heart....read more

yoga and meditation teacher

...read more

Johalys is highly experienced in mindfulness and visualization meditation. Johalys fuses ancient wisdom and modern science to craft meditations that will make lasting changes in the brain and mind.The meditations that Johalys expertly crafts are rooted in thousands of years of wisdom and backed by the latest research in neuroscience. While the teachings of ancient practices and the results of cutting-edge scientific research rest at the heart of Johalys’s guided meditations,the importance of personal experience is not lost on her. Numerous world travels have granted Johalys the opportunity to dive deeply into the collective consciousness of diverse cultures from all over the world. By acquiring a deep scientific understanding of the functions of different parts of the brain,Johalys is able to humbly accept the most effective aspects of ancient traditions that will leverage the neuroplasticity of the brain to develop permanent mindset shifts that dramatically change student’s lives....read more

As the founder of Find Your Calm, Mama, Jamie provides a safe space for stressed-out mamas/women to overcome their overwhelm, find calm and connect with themselves with meditation, mindfulness, yoga and affirmations.

She later held roles as a business consultant and technical project manager where she learned firsthand how mindfulness could increase focus, creativity and empathy. Jen founded Thought Leader to bring mindfulness to all....read more

...read more

Jessica loves to teach people the tools so they can heal themselves. Her goal is to make mindfulness and compassion practices accessible for everyone, no matter how busy they are. She believes self compassion to be the key to healing, and coupled with mindfulness, is transformational for our minds and bodies....read more

Driven by new experiences, connecting people, and a curiosity for life, Jeni is on a mission to help transform lives on a deeper level.  She made the difficult decision to leave her lucrative sales career and take the leap of faith into entrepreneurship to help professionals & entrepreneurs who are sick and tired of the day-in and day-out hustle & grind, how to find freedom, fulfillment, and reignite their joy for life!

After leaving Corporate America, Jeni has been on a spiritual and personal self-discovery that has led her to become a meditation facilitator, Reiki Level II Practitioner, and most recently a Certified Akashic Records Guide. Nearly 2 years ago, Jeni & her husband sold everything and became digital nomads and have been traveling around the USA exploring both the world internally and externally....read more

Sanadora, Angeologa, Terapeuta Reiki.

As a nutritionist, Jason uses mindfulness meditation with his clients to help them reduce their stress response, and find peace with food.  Jason has practiced meditation under a variety of teachers from several traditions. He has participated in over a dozen retreats and has practiced meditation for over 20 years....read more

Back in 2013 John was a stressed-out news reporter in New York City lacking in purpose and wanting to find more joy and meaning in his life. The best thing happened to him that year, he got fired from my dream job. It turns out that "making a living" was far from living. The day he got fired he walked into a yoga class and while he had been practicing for years, this class just hit him differently. He didn't have anywhere to be after class, no emails to answer, all he had to do was focus on himself and his breath. 

Seven years and dozens of retreats, workshops and classes around the world later, He realized this is his dharma, his life's work and his true calling. It has been his experience that this is truly some powerful medicine. 

He is someone passionate about helping people feel better and sharing what he knows and what has helped him and many others. He takes that work seriously without taking himself too seriously. He strives to always meet people where they are....read more
Grief advocate, writer, and coach.

Jenna Hollenstein is a registered dietitian, certified Intuitive Eating counselor, and meditation teacher. Jenna is the author of five books, including Eat to Love: A Mindful Guide to Transforming Your Relationship with Food, Body, and Life; Mommysattva: Contemplations for Mothers who Meditate (or wish they could); and Intuitive Eating for Life: How Mindfulness Can Deepen and Sustain Your Intuitive Eating Practice (coming December 2022)....read more

Jing Yao is a Spiritual Life Coach and Healer. She specializes in helping women in the approximate age of 40 through 60 to fulfill their highest calling in life with love, wisdom and truthfulness. She shows them how to self heal and self liberate through the cultivation of emotional freedom, so to be the fuller embodiment of Heaven, which is peace that surpasses all understanding, unconditional happiness, relentless self-love, intuitive co-creativity with the universe, and empathic mastery that transforms all and elevates all....read more

Jennifer Jennette is an educator, artist, & accidental entrepreneur. With an attitude of playful curiosity, Jen has spent years learning, teaching & creating while helping youth and adults feel connected, accepted and respected for who they are while responding to their unique needs in the moment.  
Jennifer’s foundation is in alignment-based & therapeutic yoga. Her study and practice also includes vinyasa yoga, strength training, somatic experiencing, and psychotherapy with many excellent professional yoga instructors and therapists. 
Jennifer is also an artist and maker currently designing hemp and organic cotton, yoga-inspired apparel under the name Surya Leela Designs that inspires confidence & freedom on the mat and in the world....read more

Jonas Oliver in Advanced Clinical Hypnotherapist, living in Toronto, Canada. His mission is to guide you to discover that it is possible to live a happy life, despite whatever challenges you are experiencing.

Jeff Simonton trained directly under Master Binhui He, who is recognized as one of the world's top healers.

Jeff has taught at many esteemed locations such as UNC Medical Center, UNC Wellness Centers, Duke Teer House, Rex Cancer Center and Meredith College. He has also successfully launched multiple online training programs all related to health and wellness.

After experiencing a series of traumatic events in his mid twenties Jeff went into a deep state of depression. He found himself stuck in an endless cycle of emotional and physical pain. Fortunately he took a chance on attending a 9 day healing intensive with Master He.  That intensive changed his life forever, and to this day Jeff credits those 9 days with saving his life.

Currently Jeff is getting ready to launch his new training app, Original Mind. 

If you are interested in becoming a Founding Member and helping to shape the app please visit originalmindapp.com....read more

Meditation is one of the tools I have used to help wake up my spirit and it has provided me immense comfort during more challenging periods. I am hopeful that these meditations may help you too. A natural born extra sensory Jen began to use her gifts as a young child. Which utilized meditation as the basis for all their intuitive education. She also attended Healing to Wholeness and was accredited as an Emotional Process Coach. She works with clients, teaching them how to become their own healer. And of course, meditation is a big part of this as well. 

Jen has spent her life innately dedicated to helping others find clarity, cultivating her own awareness, and finding the humor in it all along the way....read more

Founder of The Joy Method and author of The Daily Joy Journal, Jillian is a multi-passionate Joy + Mindfulness Coach who believes life is too short to wake up dreading the day ahead. As a result of past struggles with addiction, people-pleasing, and self-sacrifice, Jillian developed the practice of Joy and other tools she personally uses to support those who are ready to befriend themselves and feel better. In 2017 Jillian serendipitously stumbled into a meditation studio and her entire life changed. Now, several years later, a recovered addict and self-proclaimed "meditation nag", Jillian uses soulful strategy to teach clients, teams, and communities to align with Joy. 

Jillian’s mission is to light up the world from the inside out, while supporting, encouraging, and inspiring others to do the same. Read more at jillianschecher.com...read more

Hello lovely listeners. In today’s world we are all faced with so many unique challenges. They might be relational, they might be financial, they might be emotional…. No matter what anyone’s struggles are, the world of psychology now knows that these difficulties take place in us - not just in our minds, but in our bodies. And the way to heal, to release that tension, to move forwards, is to reconnect our bodies with our minds. How? A combination of moving our bodies with awareness of breath, and processing our emotions with a deeper understanding of our own minds. My training as a psychologist and yoga teacher have helped me help others, and I am pleased to share these techniques with you, all aimed at reconnecting with ourselves, promoting peace of mind and relaxation, and being able to cope and deal with the pressures of modern life.
